The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Kwara State has promised to reward Offa community with key positions if its candidates are elected in the general elections. Chairman of the party in the state, Babatunde Mohammed, disclosed this at the party’s secretariat in Ilorin while receiving APC defectors from across 10 political wards in Offa LGA. Muhammed urged the new PDP members to canvass votes for all the party’s candidates, assuring that a PDP-led government would reward the people of Offa with key positions. Man arraigned over N115,000 fraud Gov’ship candidates to defend agenda at Media Trust debate in Kano The Director General of the PDP Gubernatorial Campaign Council in Kwara, Prof Ali Ahmad, said the success of PDP at the polls would bring good fortune to Offa and Kwara State in general. 